$ Oracle SQL: select - group by clause
@ group by

{ listagg #group-by_listagg

 `listagg` allows to concatenate values of different records that belong to the same group into *one* record.

 `listagg` is defined in the → misc/ISO/9075/features/T625[optional SQL feature T625].

  → development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/19c improves `listagg` with a `distinct` clause.

  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQL/select/group_by/listagg.sql||


}
sa:

  Oracle does not allow to → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/data-types/lob#ora-lob-group-by[group by LOB columnns].

  The → development/databases/SQL/select/group-by[SQL `group by` clause].

